						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 35, Vikṛita, Pushya, śu. 13, Ādivāra, Uttarāyaṇa-saṅkrānti, Vyatīpāta</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1110 December 25 Sunday.</hi> It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva.</hi> It states that the <hi rend="italic">Daṇḍādhipati</hi> <hi rend="bold">Muddarasa</hi> or Muddarāja made some grant for the tank Nāgasamudra near <hi rend="bold">Sōge.</hi></p>						

